VALUES
(40, 9, 36, 24, 50, 6, 6, 'sheep having no shepherd', 'Compassion for Lost Sheep', 'Both passages emphasize the plight of lost sheep and the absence of proper shepherds. Matthew highlights Jesus'' compassion for the scattered multitudes, while Jeremiah laments that the shepherds have caused the people to go astray.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 36, 26, 34, 3, 6, 'as sheep having no shepherd', 'Compassion for the Scattered Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the plight of the scattered sheep without a shepherd. Matthew''s depiction of Jesus'' compassion mirrors Ezekiel''s lament over the neglect of the flock by their leaders.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 36, 40, 14, 14, 14, 'moved with compassion', 'Compassion for the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the multitudes. In each instance, He is moved with compassion and responds to their needs, highlighting His role as a shepherd to the scattered people.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 36, 38, 10, 2, 2, 'as sheep having no shepherd', 'Compassion and Shepherd Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being ''scattered'' and lacking a shepherd. Matthew highlights Jesus'' compassion for the ''multitudes'' who are ''as sheep having no shepherd,'' while Zechariah describes a flock that is ''troubled, because there was no shepherd.'' This connection highlights the need for guidance and care.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 36, 14, 18, 16, 16, 'as sheep having no shepherd', 'Compassion for the Scattered', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of being ''scattered as sheep having no shepherd.'' This connection highlights the concern for those without guidance and the need for leadership.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 42, 10, 2, 2, 'the harvest truly is plenteous', 'Connection of Harvest and Laborers', 'Both passages emphasize the abundance of the harvest and the scarcity of laborers. They highlight the need for prayer to send more laborers into the harvest.', 'theme', 0.671, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 41, 16, 15, 15, 'the harvest truly is plenteous', 'Call to Action for Laborers', 'Both passages emphasize the need for action in spreading the gospel. Matthew highlights the few laborers available for a plentiful harvest, while Mark commands the disciples to go and preach to all.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 46, 3, 9, 9, 'the labourers are few', 'Connection of Labor and Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of laborers in God''s work. Matthew highlights the need for more laborers for the harvest, while 1 Corinthians describes believers as laborers together with God.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 43, 4, 35, 36, 'the harvest truly is plenteous', 'Connection of Harvest Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of harvest, highlighting the urgency and abundance of the fields ready for gathering. The call for laborers in Matthew aligns with the invitation to look at the fields in John, suggesting a shared theme of readiness for spiritual work.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 40, 28, 19, 19, 'labourers are few', 'Connection of Laborers and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the call to action in both passages. The ''labourers'' in the harvest are those who are sent to ''teach all nations,'' emphasizing the need for active participation in spreading the message.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 42, 24, 47, 47, 'the harvest truly is plenteous', 'Connection of Harvest and Preaching', 'This connection highlights the urgency of laborers needed for the spiritual harvest. Both passages emphasize the need for action in spreading the message of repentance and remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 37, 47, 6, 1, 1, 'labourers are few', 'Connection of Laborers and Workers', 'Both passages emphasize the role of workers in God''s mission. Matthew highlights the need for laborers, while 2 Corinthians calls believers to work together with God, suggesting a shared responsibility in the harvest.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 42, 10, 1, 2, 'pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest', 'Connection of Laborers and Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the need for laborers in the harvest. They share the same call to pray to the Lord of the harvest for more workers, highlighting the urgency of the mission.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 24, 3, 15, 15, 'labourers into his harvest', 'Connection of Pastors and Labourers', 'Both passages emphasize the need for leaders who provide guidance and support. Matthew calls for ''labourers'' to be sent, while Jeremiah promises ''pastors'' who will feed with knowledge.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 53, 3, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Prayer for Laborers', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer for the advancement of God''s work. Matthew encourages prayer for laborers, while 2 Thessalonians requests prayer for the word of the Lord to spread effectively.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 44, 13, 2, 2, 'send forth labourers into his harvest', 'Call for Laborers in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine calling for laborers in ministry. In Matthew, there is a prayer for the Lord to send forth laborers, while Acts describes the Holy Ghost calling specific individuals for work.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 43, 20, 21, 21, 'send forth labourers into his harvest', 'Sending of Laborers', 'This connection highlights the theme of being sent. In Matthew, Jesus calls for laborers to be sent into the harvest, while in John, He directly sends His disciples as He was sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 44, 8, 4, 4, 'send forth labourers into his harvest', 'Laborers in the Harvest', 'This connection highlights the call for laborers in Matthew 9:38 and the fulfillment of that call in Acts 8:4, where those scattered preached the word. Both passages emphasize the importance of spreading the message of the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 9, 38, 46, 12, 28, 28, 'labourers into his harvest', 'Laborers in the Church', 'This connection highlights the call for laborers in the harvest and the roles established within the church. Both passages emphasize the importance of individuals working in service to God, whether in the harvest field or within the church community.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 42, 9, 1, 6, 'power against unclean spirits', 'Empowerment of the Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the empowerment given to the disciples to heal and cast out unclean spirits. They highlight the authority bestowed upon them to preach and perform miracles as part of their mission.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 41, 3, 13, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the twelve disciples to heal sicknesses and cast out devils. This connection highlights the commissioning of the disciples for ministry and their empowerment to confront evil.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 41, 6, 7, 13, 'gave them power against unclean spirits', 'Disciples'' Empowerment for Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the empowerment of the disciples to cast out unclean spirits and heal the sick. This connection highlights the commissioning of the twelve disciples for their ministry work.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 42, 10, 19, 19, 'power against unclean spirits', 'Power Over Evil Forces', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine empowerment given to the disciples. Both passages emphasize the authority to overcome evil, with Matthew focusing on healing and casting out spirits, while Luke expands this to include protection against all enemies.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'power', 'Power Given for Witnessing', 'Both passages emphasize the granting of power to the disciples. In Matthew, they receive power to heal and cast out spirits, while in Acts, they receive power to be witnesses. This connection highlights the continuity of divine empowerment for ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 43, 3, 27, 27, 'power against unclean spirits', 'Divine Authority and Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine empowerment. In Matthew, Jesus gives his disciples power, while in John, it is stated that one can receive nothing unless it is given from heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 1, 40, 28, 18, 19, 'power against unclean spirits', 'Empowerment for Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of empowerment given to the disciples. In Matthew 10:1, they receive power to heal and cast out spirits, while in Matthew 28:18-19, Jesus emphasizes that all power is given to him, sending them to teach and baptize.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 2, 40, 4, 21, 21, 'James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother', 'Connection of Apostolic Names', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between James and John as brothers and apostles. Matthew 10:2 lists them as apostles, while Matthew 4:21 describes their calling by Jesus.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 2, 44, 1, 13, 13, NULL, 'Apostles'' Names Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the names of the apostles, specifically mentioning Peter, James, and John. This connection highlights the continuity of the apostolic group from Jesus'' ministry to the early church.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 2, 42, 5, 10, 10, 'James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother', 'Connection of Apostles and Partnership', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Simon and the sons of Zebedee, James and John, highlighting their partnership in fishing before becoming apostles. This connection illustrates their shared calling and the transition from fishing to ''catching men.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 2, 43, 6, 8, 8, 'Andrew his brother', 'Connection of Andrew and Peter', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Andrew and Simon Peter, highlighting Andrew as Simon Peter''s brother. This connection illustrates their roles among the apostles.', 'keyword', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
